Event tap code injection not yet implemented

This test currently "passes" with Koru being 3x faster than baseline,
but that's because the taps aren't actually running!

Expected output:
  Baseline: Taps called: 25
  Koru:     Taps called: 25  (should match!)

Actual output:
  Baseline: Taps called: 25
  Koru:     Taps called: 0   (taps not firing!)

From EVENT_TAPS.md Phase 4:
  "Code Generation: Identify event invocation sites and inject tap code"
  Status: NOT IMPLEMENTED YET

Once tap injection is implemented, this test will:
- Start showing ~3.5ms for both (same work)
- Prove taps have same overhead as manual function calls
- Validate the "zero-cost" claim (no dispatch overhead)

Until then, this test documents that taps need implementation!
